column4: Hi, can anyone give me any ideas as to why my bios is reporting that I've overclocked my cpu from 2.67 to 3.20 but ubuntu is reporting that my upper limit is 2.67 still?
Have you gone back to check the settings held?
well, thanks for at least responding
it's more than I've gotten other places
Meh... annoyingly I'm not even on my ubuntu laptop atm
I assume you're not dual booting?
I am, but I rarely if ever use windows
This is a crappy idea... but boot into windows and see what that says?
If that has the overclocked values, we can be pretty sure hardware is fine, ubuntu needs kicking
